On July 28, a large amount of tourists gathered to take a look at the Hukou Waterfall of the Yellow River in the scenic area in Jixian County of Shanxi Province. Recently, dueÂ to excessive rainfall, the waterfall has embraced large amounts of water that enables roaring, which attracts tourists to take pictures. Hukou Waterfall, known as the largest yellow waterfall in the world, is located at the intersection of Shaanxi Province and Shanxi Province. (All images via CFP) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)